boss to change.

00:39:01.970 --> 00:39:06.170
There's this constant arguing with reality
of who you know people to be.

00:39:06.170 --> 00:39:07.480
No more.

00:39:07.480 --> 00:39:10.990
There's an arguing of reality of what's going
on in the external environment.

00:39:10.990 --> 00:39:15.680
Do you know the energy it takes to argue with
reality all the time?

00:39:15.680 --> 00:39:20.480
It's like being in a flowing river, where
you know life is taking you exactly on the

00:39:20.480 --> 00:39:22.710
journey you're supposed to be on.

00:39:22.710 --> 00:39:29.380
And when you, when life changes, or when you
know reality drops in, you do one of two things.

00:39:29.380 --> 00:39:33.800
You're in the flowing river, you hang on to
the first rock or boulder, right?

00:39:33.800 --> 00:39:35.210
I'm not gonna go forward.

00:39:35.210 --> 00:39:38.090
I don't like what this relationship's now
gonna look at.

00:39:38.090 --> 00:39:40.840
I don't like what this work is now gonna possibly
be.

00:39:40.840 --> 00:39:45.270
So you're kind of holding, you're resisting
where life is actually already gonna take

00:39:45.270 --> 00:39:46.560
you.

00:39:46.560 --> 00:39:48.340
Or you might be in another category.

00:39:48.340 --> 00:39:50.800
You start rowing back upstream.

00:39:50.800 --> 00:39:52.240
I want the body back.

00:39:52.240 --> 00:39:53.750
I want the relationship back.

00:39:53.750 --> 00:39:56.870
I want the money back that I lost in the stock
market.

00:39:56.870 --> 00:39:58.900
So there's a sense of like going backwards.

00:39:58.900 --> 00:40:03.470
But when you're not in a place of sort of
I'm accepting the way it is, you're either

00:40:03.470 --> 00:40:06.720
stuck in the paralysis or you're living in
the past.

00:40:06.720 --> 00:40:08.230
It's one of those two things.

00:40:08.230 --> 00:40:13.210
But it's never you know it's not the actual
change that's hard, again it's the energy

00:40:13.210 --> 00:40:17.970
that you had invested in, my life is gonna
look/be a certain way.

00:40:17.970 --> 00:40:23.710
So you know I always ask the question, what
is the one change or the one thing in your

00:40:23.710 --> 00:40:26.060
life that you still have not accepted?

00:40:26.060 --> 00:40:28.680
Because that also has tremendous power over
you.

00:40:28.680 --> 00:40:31.060
You know is it something someone said?

00:40:31.060 --> 00:40:32.590
Is it something someone did?

00:40:32.590 --> 00:40:35.540
What's that one thing that you really need
to accept?

00:40:35.540 --> 00:40:37.620
Something about yourself?

00:40:37.620 --> 00:40:40.720
Something you still feel you know, I should
be different.

00:40:40.720 --> 00:40:44.210
We all, we have such a should program on us.

00:40:44.210 --> 00:40:45.750
We have a should program.

00:40:45.750 --> 00:40:47.810
We have a comparison program.

00:40:47.810 --> 00:40:49.950
We have a competition program on us.

00:40:49.950 --> 00:40:51.960
We're, we're covered in programs.

00:40:51.960 --> 00:40:57.190
And one of those programs is basically holding
you very hostage of you not being able to

00:40:57.190 --> 00:40:59.220
move forward when a change happens.

00:40:59.220 --> 00:41:03.340
[sound of drinking water]

00:41:03.340 --> 00:41:08.570
Just so you know, the three most dominant
programs you have as human beings, this comes

00:41:08.570 --> 00:41:11.830
from years of research, are three things.

00:41:11.830 --> 00:41:14.480
The first one is love and approval.

00:41:14.480 --> 00:41:16.770
The second one is control.

00:41:16.770 --> 00:41:20.130
And the third one is safety.

00:41:20.130 --> 00:41:24.400
Everything you do is to meet one of these
three programs.

00:41:24.400 --> 00:41:25.869
Why you work here.

00:41:25.869 --> 00:41:28.560
Who you're married to or why you're single.

00:41:28.560 --> 00:41:33.530
Why you eat or take care of your health the
way you do is to meet one of these three programs.

00:41:33.530 --> 00:41:36.740
You, you can see it in your colleagues and
your friends.

00:41:36.740 --> 00:41:38.890
What is their dominant program?

00:41:38.890 --> 00:41:41.710
Are they love and approval seekers?

00:41:41.710 --> 00:41:45.650
Are they control people or I call them freaks?

00:41:45.650 --> 00:41:47.410
Are they safety people?

00:41:47.410 --> 00:41:48.410
Safe.

00:41:48.410 --> 00:41:49.410
Safe.

00:41:49.410 --> 00:41:50.410
Safe.

00:41:50.410 --> 00:41:51.410
Right?

00:41:51.410 --> 00:41:52.410
Everything needs to be safe.

00:41:52.410 --> 00:41:55.040
If you can just see what is the dominant program
even in the people you work with and the people

00:41:55.040 --> 00:42:00.599
you live with, you can meet them much more
at what is their dominant program.

00:42:00.599 --> 00:42:02.010
They're wired this way.

00:42:02.010 --> 00:42:08.170
And the thing you need to remember is once
you know what your own program is, most people,

00:42:08.170 --> 00:42:13.350
for example if they are in love and approval,
they will do anything to get love and approval.

00:42:13.350 --> 00:42:19.000
And the paradox with life is, the more you
move towards it, the more it moves away.

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:22.490
So the more I want love and approval, the
more it walks out the door.

00:42:22.490 --> 00:42:26.300
The more I don't really need love and approval,
the more life kind of gives you it in bucket

00:42:26.300 --> 00:42:27.300
loads.

00:42:27.300 --> 00:42:31.470
The more you try and control life, you try
and control people, your environment, the

00:42:31.470 --> 00:42:35.380
project, the work, the more control moves
away from you.

00:42:35.380 --> 00:42:38.010
So being aware of what is your dominant program.

00:42:38.010 --> 00:42:42.650
Because when life changes, it hits one of
these three programs.

00:42:42.650 --> 00:42:47.990
Either love and approval's been chopped by
someone or something, your control's gone

00:42:47.990 --> 00:42:53.400
out the door and you don't feel safe, but
one of them is most obvious.

00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:58.430
And being able to rest in and remember, the
more I try and get safe, the more I'm gonna

00:42:58.430 --> 00:42:59.970
feel unsafe.

00:42:59.970 --> 00:43:02.609
That's all just on that particular point,
just remember.

00:43:02.609 --> 00:43:06.869
And start noticing in other people, oh that
behavior is really about you know control

00:43:06.869 --> 00:43:11.369
or it's really about safety, leading me right
into the next one.

00:43:11.369 --> 00:43:16.660
Principle number six are the things you can
control when you're going through a life change.

00:43:16.660 --> 00:43:20.690
So when things change everything feels very
out of control.

00:43:20.690 --> 00:43:22.530
And as I said earlier, we do one thing.

00:43:22.530 --> 00:43:26.090
We try and sort of change things on the outside.

00:43:26.090 --> 00:43:29.930
The only thing you can control is your inner
world.

00:43:29.930 --> 00:43:32.340
What do I mean by that specifically?

00:43:32.340 --> 00:43:35.360
Your language and words.

00:43:35.360 --> 00:43:37.540
The questions you ask yourself.

00:43:37.540 --> 00:43:40.830
The stories you tell yourself and other people.

00:43:40.830 --> 00:43:42.540
That's what I got from the people that I interviewed.

00:43:42.540 --> 00:43:45.040
So I'll give you an example.

00:43:45.040 --> 00:43:48.070
I interviewed people who had lost their jobs.

00:43:48.070 --> 00:43:49.580
The language that they used.

00:43:49.580 --> 00:43:51.310
The words that they used.

00:43:51.310 --> 00:43:54.940
Of people that got through the change and
people who didn't.

00:43:54.940 --> 00:44:03.040
People who are good at change do not use words
like disaster, nightmare, worst day ever,

00:44:03.040 --> 00:44:06.030
crazy, horrific week.

00:44:06.030 --> 00:44:07.800
They don't have that language.

00:44:07.800 --> 00:44:10.780
They have a very different vocabulary.

00:44:10.780 --> 00:44:13.660
So one of the things I'd invite you to look
at, whether you're going through a change

00:44:13.660 --> 00:44:16.780
or you're not at this point, are what are
your go-to words?

00:44:16.780 --> 00:44:19.630
Like where are you sloppy with your words?

00:44:19.630 --> 00:44:24.470
Where are you sort of just quite casual about
throwing out very negatively charged emotional

00:44:24.470 --> 00:44:25.859
words?

00:44:25.859 --> 00:44:28.820
In work, in your personal environment, towards
yourself.

00:44:28.820 --> 00:44:33.270
Because again, having the awareness of and
if you don't I can guarantee your friends

00:44:33.270 --> 00:44:36.430
and colleagues can tell you because you use
these words all the time, you're not even

00:44:36.430 --> 00:44:37.450
aware of them.

00:44:37.450 --> 00:44:42.920
But where, where's just be very, have a finesse
about what the words are.

00:44:42.920 --> 00:44:47.040
People who are good at change use words like
opportunity, lesson, this is a challenge,

00:44:47.040 --> 00:44:51.380
you know I'm really being asked to step up
and look at something differently, but they

00:44:51.380 --> 00:44:54.090
don't have this negative tirade of words.

00:44:54.090 --> 00:44:55.880
Same thing with questions.

00:44:55.880 --> 00:44:59.480
You know if you ask your mind a question,
it's gonna answer it.

00:44:59.480 --> 00:45:01.850
So if you go why did this happen to me?

00:45:01.850 --> 00:45:02.990
Why am I so unlucky?

00:45:02.990 --> 00:45:04.450
Why is this guy such a jerk?

00:45:04.450 --> 00:45:06.240
Why is this a woman such a whatever?

00:45:06.240 --> 00:45:09.810
Your mind's gonna answer that and you're gonna
kind of feel ok well that must be the truth

00:45:09.810 --> 00:45:12.180
because my mind answered it.

00:45:12.180 --> 00:45:15.380
People who are good at change have a very
different level of questions.

00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:17.730
How can this be a good thing?

00:45:17.730 --> 00:45:21.570
How can I find some humor in this, this is
so crazy?

00:45:21.570 --> 00:45:23.400
Who can help me?

00:45:23.400 --> 00:45:26.340
Great question to ask yourself when you're
going through a change, which is not your

00:45:26.340 --> 00:45:28.310
typical normal question.

00:45:28.310 --> 00:45:31.250
You do have control over the questions that
you keep asking yourself.

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:38.070
And the final thing you can control, which
is so powerful, are the stories you tell yourself.

00:45:38.070 --> 00:45:41.090
We are a walking library of stories.

00:45:41.090 --> 00:45:46.800
You have a story about yourself, your weight
or why you can't lose it, how you are at work,

00:45:46.800 --> 00:45:51.161
about men, about women, about your parents,
about why they're together, about why they

00:45:51.161 --> 00:45:55.690
got divorced, about religion, about, you have
a story about everything.

00:45:55.690 --> 00:45:58.590
You actually are a walking library of stories.

00:45:58.590 --> 00:46:00.880
Your stories are not the facts.

00:46:00.880 --> 00:46:03.609
Your stories are a story about what happened.

00:46:03.609 --> 00:46:08.020
But there's again an addiction to sort of
holding on to here is the library of my life

00:46:08.020 --> 00:46:10.430
and no one's gonna touch it.

00:46:10.430 --> 00:46:13.150
If you want a new story of any kind.

00:46:13.150 --> 00:46:14.570
If you want a new change.

00:46:14.570 --> 00:46:18.660
If you want a, if you're going through a change
and you want to look at it differently, you

00:46:18.660 --> 00:46:23.730
need to take one of these stories and actually
create some space in your library for a new

00:46:23.730 --> 00:46:27.210
story, not hold the story.

00:46:27.210 --> 00:46:31.570
If you don't know what your stories are, again
I guarantee you, just ask your friends or

00:46:31.570 --> 00:46:32.910
people you work with.

00:46:32.910 --> 00:46:35.300
You have a story about why you're single.

00:46:35.300 --> 00:46:37.500
You have a story about why you can't lose
weight.

00:46:37.500 --> 00:46:42.390
And I promise you, your friends are bored
with your story.

00:46:42.390 --> 00:46:44.880
And I know this from very personal experience.

00:46:44.880 --> 00:46:47.240
I used to have stories about being single.

00:46:47.240 --> 00:46:48.550
Men in New York.

00:46:48.550 --> 00:46:49.550
My parents.

00:46:49.550 --> 00:46:52.090
Like I was a walking library of stories.

00:46:52.090 --> 00:46:54.330
Until some pretty good friends kind of go,
you know what?

00:46:54.330 --> 00:46:58.350
I'm really bored with the story about men
in New York.

00:46:58.350 --> 00:46:59.350
And so you know what?

00:46:59.350 --> 00:47:00.350
I had a choice.

00:47:00.350 --> 00:47:03.980
I could fight the friend, who she was happily
married, of course, right?

00:47:03.980 --> 00:47:07.470
I could fight the friend or I could actually
take it on and kind of go you know what, you're

00:47:07.470 --> 00:47:08.470
right.

00:47:08.470 --> 00:47:11.330
I have a really big story about that particular
issue.

00:47:11.330 --> 00:47:15.440
And it's funny and I bring it up, but I promise
you, you have a story that you are also holding

00:47:15.440 --> 00:47:18.840
onto for dear life because you think it's
the truth.

00:47:18.840 --> 00:47:19.840
It's not the truth.

00:47:19.840 --> 00:47:21.450
It's your story about it.

00:47:21.450 --> 00:47:27.670
So when you're going through change, you know
there's a sense of again controlling the outside.

00:47:27.670 --> 00:47:28.670
Turn it in.

00:47:28.670 --> 00:47:33.240
You control yourself, watch how quickly your
external environment changes.

00:47:33.240 --> 00:47:34.510
It's fascinating.

00:47:34.510 --> 00:47:36.380
It's not anything we've been told.

00:47:36.380 --> 00:47:39.970
We're told that you know, you move around
things on the outside and then you get to

00:47:39.970 --> 00:47:40.970
feel better.

00:47:40.970 --> 00:47:42.350
No, no, no, no, no.

00:47:42.350 --> 00:47:46.310
You get to feel better and the outside tends
to sort of shift around.

00:47:46.310 --> 00:47:47.310
Put it to the test.

00:47:47.310 --> 00:47:50.620
I'm just, I'm inviting you to actually look
at the effect of that.

00:47:50.620 --> 00:47:53.000
Principle number seven.

00:47:53.000 --> 00:47:56.770
Principle number seven is what I call your
spiritual side.

00:47:56.770 --> 00:48:01.609
Every person I interviewed going through change
that had found their courage and had found

00:48:01.609 --> 00:48:07.270
their strength and had found their inspiration
referred to something to do with their spirituality

00:48:07.270 --> 00:48:08.770
or religion.

00:48:08.770 --> 00:48:11.450
They definitely didn't all agree on what they
called it.

00:48:11.450 --> 00:48:16.800
Some called it grace, some called it presence,
some called it God, some called it Buddha,

00:48:16.800 --> 00:48:21.290
some called it life, the universe, but they
all agreed in one thing.

00:48:21.290 --> 00:48:23.359
Something bigger is going on here.

00:48:23.359 --> 00:48:25.420
I don't know why I'm in this change.

00:48:25.420 --> 00:48:26.460
It's crazy.

00:48:26.460 --> 00:48:27.460
It's difficult.

00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:28.460
It's amazing.

00:48:28.460 --> 00:48:29.460
I'm overwhelmed.

00:48:29.460 --> 00:48:30.810
Whatever it is, you know?

00:48:30.810 --> 00:48:35.690
We all have sort of the, the, the change is
a particular way story going on.

00:48:35.690 --> 00:48:40.000
But they had a sense of, I don't know what
it is but I feel like something bigger is

00:48:40.000 --> 00:48:41.349
happening here.

00:48:41.349 --> 00:48:46.770
And so trusting in the, the something bigger,
whatever that is for you.

00:48:46.770 --> 00:48:52.070
But change is always an invitation to sort
of get connected with that part which very

00:48:52.070 --> 00:48:56.849
often when life is all rosy and happy, we
tend to forget about that part.

00:48:56.849 --> 00:49:01.839
We tend to step into it as an invitation where,
oh I actually need to connect a little bit

00:49:01.839 --> 00:49:03.510
more with that.

00:49:03.510 --> 00:49:05.630
Again you name it what you want.

00:49:05.630 --> 00:49:10.420
One of the number one ways I would suggest
people to do it is just to find stillness.

00:49:10.420 --> 00:49:14.119
Find silence of any kind at any time.

00:49:14.119 --> 00:49:15.630
Five minutes, ten minutes, twenty minutes.

00:49:15.630 --> 00:49:19.720
And I can tell you, if you do not have 20
minutes in your day to be still, there's something

00:49:19.720 --> 00:49:22.220
wrong with your day.

00:49:22.220 --> 00:49:26.890
There's gotta, you've gotta find it, ten,
fifteen minutes of just stillness.

00:49:26.890 --> 00:49:28.150
No distractions.

00:49:28.150 --> 00:49:29.410
No busyness.

00:49:29.410 --> 00:49:32.820
Because if you can't, I would invite you to
sort of say, well what is it that you don't

00:49:32.820 --> 00:49:34.369
wanna hear?

00:49:34.369 --> 00:49:35.960
What is it that you don't wanna listen?

00:49:35.960 --> 00:49:39.130
Why, why is silence so scary?

00:49:39.130 --> 00:49:43.990
Like I, I make it what I call a non-negotiable
and I would invite you all to look at your

00:49:43.990 --> 00:49:46.109
non-negotiables and pick a couple.

00:49:46.109 --> 00:49:50.480
What are the things that you don't negotiate
for anything?

00:49:50.480 --> 00:49:54.609
Not your kids, not your boss, not your parents,
not anyone?

00:49:54.609 --> 00:49:55.609
What are you non-negotiables?

00:49:55.609 --> 00:49:59.600
My non-negotiables are my spiritual path and
my health.

00:49:59.600 --> 00:50:01.109
No one touches those.

00:50:01.109 --> 00:50:02.109
And guess what?

00:50:02.109 --> 00:50:06.960
When you create a bit of a sacred space around
whatever those non-negotiables are, life tends

00:50:06.960 --> 00:50:12.849
to keep you away from them, it's fine, because
you've actually taken a stand for them.

00:50:12.849 --> 00:50:18.160
But find that you know when everything in
your life is changing, you have to find something

00:50:18.160 --> 00:50:19.609
that doesn't change.

00:50:19.609 --> 00:50:20.740
You have to.

00:50:20.740 --> 00:50:25.170
And a lot of the times when you're going through
one change, life does a really funny thing.

00:50:25.170 --> 00:50:27.211
It brings two or three more changes with it.

00:50:27.211 --> 00:50:28.211
Right?

00:50:28.211 --> 00:50:29.211
It's natural.

00:50:29.211 --> 00:50:32.490
Your job changes and now your relationships
also change.

00:50:32.490 --> 00:50:36.660
Your money's changing and now you know your
home something is changing as well.

00:50:36.660 --> 00:50:40.330
So life tends to bring with it more than one
change at a time.

00:50:40.330 --> 00:50:45.160
It's my number one thing I would say, when
you're in a change, you need to find a place

00:50:45.160 --> 00:50:47.960
that is what I call the silent witness.

00:50:47.960 --> 00:50:53.670
The silent observer that can kind of see but
not be part of the change.

00:50:53.670 --> 00:50:57.100
And the it the biggest way to get in touch
with that is to meditate.

00:50:57.100 --> 00:51:01.710
And if meditation's a scary word, it's just
to sit in silence and just to sort of watch,

00:51:01.710 --> 00:51:02.710
watch your thoughts.

00:51:02.710 --> 00:51:03.710
You don't even need to get involved.

00:51:03.710 --> 00:51:08.180
You don't need to entertain them, but there's
a real invitation to do, you know, if it's

00:51:08.180 --> 00:51:10.270
not meditation, go into nature.

00:51:10.270 --> 00:51:13.400
If it's not nature, start journaling.

00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:18.820
But there's plenty of ways to sort of get
in touch with that more spiritual core.

00:51:18.820 --> 00:51:20.690
Ok.

00:51:20.690 --> 00:51:21.720
Principle number eight.

00:51:21.720 --> 00:51:26.151
So much more I could have said on spirituality,
but-- Principle number eight is what I call

00:51:26.151 --> 00:51:29.740
your change support team.

00:51:29.740 --> 00:51:32.589
People who are good at change are not alone.

00:51:32.589 --> 00:51:35.010
I'd say it's our biggest flaw as human beings.

00:51:35.010 --> 00:51:37.390
We keep thinking we're alone.

00:51:37.390 --> 00:51:39.840
I'm the only one going through this change.

00:51:39.840 --> 00:51:42.170
No one has ever felt this bad.

00:51:42.170 --> 00:51:44.660
No one has ever eaten this much ice cream.

00:51:44.660 --> 00:51:47.089
No one has ever cried so much on the couch.

00:51:47.089 --> 00:51:49.530
No one has ever been so heart broken for so
long.

00:51:49.530 --> 00:51:51.700
Like, we, we do this all the time.

00:51:51.700 --> 00:51:54.700
No one has ever messed up as much as I have.

00:51:54.700 --> 00:51:57.580
No one has ever, you know, it's like the list
continues.

00:51:57.580 --> 00:51:59.330
But we have the sense that we're alone.

00:51:59.330 --> 00:52:00.710
I'm the only one.

00:52:00.710 --> 00:52:02.029
And what does that do?

00:52:02.029 --> 00:52:05.210
That separates us once again from life.

00:52:05.210 --> 00:52:06.970
It separates us from people.

00:52:06.970 --> 00:52:09.030
It separates us from people who could be helping.

00:52:09.030 --> 00:52:13.770
So just ask yourself, are you, are you a bit
of a I'm alone person?

00:52:13.770 --> 00:52:18.030
Because if you are you're gonna make your
life really difficult because life is a combination

00:52:18.030 --> 00:52:19.859
of changes.

00:52:19.859 --> 00:52:20.859
Here's what's interesting.

00:52:20.859 --> 00:52:26.950
When you do go through change, your change
support team are not necessarily the people

00:52:26.950 --> 00:52:30.260
you would naturally go to.

00:52:30.260 --> 00:52:34.830
You know, when you go through change I don't
necessarily recommend calling your mother.

00:52:34.830 --> 00:52:37.349
Not a good idea.

00:52:37.349 --> 00:52:42.500
She loves you, she's on your love team, but
she's not necessarily on your change team.

00:52:42.500 --> 00:52:46.150
She's gonna be worried and she's gonna ask
you a million questions and five days later

00:52:46.150 --> 00:52:50.460
when you're kind of better, she's still worrying
about your change.

00:52:50.460 --> 00:52:56.190
So when you're going through a change, be
very mindful of who you're gonna call.

00:52:56.190 --> 00:52:58.839
Who actually can help you?

00:52:58.839 --> 00:53:00.210
Who's on your change team?

00:53:00.210 --> 00:53:03.330
They're not your closest friends, partners,
husbands, wives.

00:53:03.330 --> 00:53:05.980
They are gonna be quite shaken by your change.

00:53:05.980 --> 00:53:10.119
The most beautiful thing is when you go through
change new people tend to show up in your

00:53:10.119 --> 00:53:12.859
life who have no idea who you are.

00:53:12.859 --> 00:53:17.640
They don't have this fixed identity of you
know Mike is this or Ann is that.

00:53:17.640 --> 00:53:20.359
There's sort of a freedom about who and what
you are.

00:53:20.359 --> 00:53:24.050
They don't know how many times you've tried
to lose weight or how many tries you've tried

00:53:24.050 --> 00:53:28.710
to stop smoking or how many times you've messed
up doing a particular thing.

00:53:28.710 --> 00:53:30.290
There's a neutrality about them.

00:53:30.290 --> 00:53:36.020
But be very careful, you know I always say
look at the five people that you spend the

00:53:36.020 --> 00:53:38.109
most amount of time with.

00:53:38.109 --> 00:53:43.780
Five people you spend the most amount of time
with have a massive influence on your life.

00:53:43.780 --> 00:53:44.780
Massive.

00:53:44.780 --> 00:53:45.900
In every regard.

00:53:45.900 --> 00:53:47.290
Who are your five people?

00:53:47.290 --> 00:53:52.690
Because we're very casual about who influences
us when we're going through change.

00:53:52.690 --> 00:53:54.710
And you don't get good advice.

00:53:54.710 --> 00:54:01.070
You get their beliefs and their opinions and
their fears and their conditioning.

00:54:01.070 --> 00:54:02.690
That's not advice.

00:54:02.690 --> 00:54:05.710
That's their stuff that they need to go work
through.

00:54:05.710 --> 00:54:10.330
There's two types of people that I would say
you, you find when you go through change.

00:54:10.330 --> 00:54:12.700
People that get in the hole with you, right?

00:54:12.700 --> 00:54:15.300
You're in the hole, they go in the hole with
you.

00:54:15.300 --> 00:54:16.800
He's such a jerk.

00:54:16.800 --> 00:54:18.830
Absolutely she should never have done that.

00:54:18.830 --> 00:54:20.620
I can't believe he did that to you.

00:54:20.620 --> 00:54:21.620
Right?

00:54:21.620 --> 00:54:23.080
There's people that agree with you.

00:54:23.080 --> 00:54:27.390
And they kind of casually somewhat make you
feel better for about half a second.

00:54:27.390 --> 00:54:29.662
And they're very often the people that drag
you for a drink.

00:54:29.662 --> 00:54:32.950
Let's drink it away or let's eat it away.

00:54:32.950 --> 00:54:35.359
Because they actually don't know quite how
to deal with it, right?

00:54:35.359 --> 00:54:36.930
But they're not comfortable.

00:54:36.930 --> 00:54:41.020
And some of you might be these kind of people,
which is sort of like, oooh my girl, my friend,

00:54:41.020 --> 00:54:46.089
my partner's going through a change, I'm gonna
try and you know distract them in some way.

00:54:46.089 --> 00:54:50.120
But some people walk right in the hole with
you and they don't, they're not very helpful.

00:54:50.120 --> 00:54:54.640
So don't surround yourself with those people,
who all they do is agree with you.

00:54:54.640 --> 00:54:57.590
You want people who are what I call ladder
people.

00:54:57.590 --> 00:55:02.850
They see you in a hole, they hand you a ladder
and somehow they get you up the ladder.

00:55:02.850 --> 00:55:06.589
And you resist those people because it's much
more comfortable being in the hole.

00:55:06.589 --> 00:55:09.070
You get attention.

00:55:09.070 --> 00:55:10.070
You get compassion.

00:55:10.070 --> 00:55:11.460
You get, you know, validation.

00:55:11.460 --> 00:55:14.240
But get people who are actually gonna walk
you up the ladder.

00:55:14.240 --> 00:55:16.090
Those are the most important things.

00:55:16.090 --> 00:55:17.700
So that's change support team.

00:55:17.700 --> 00:55:23.910
Be, just be mindful of who's on your team,
you know, if you're thinking about making

00:55:23.910 --> 00:55:27.050
a change, who has made that change before
you?

00:55:27.050 --> 00:55:29.170
That would be a great person to go to.

00:55:29.170 --> 00:55:33.890
Most people if they've been through a cancer
diagnosis, they want to help.

00:55:33.890 --> 00:55:36.770
If someone has started a business, they want
to help.

00:55:36.770 --> 00:55:39.410
If someone's lost weight, they want to help.

00:55:39.410 --> 00:55:41.300
Who needs to be on your change team?

00:55:41.300 --> 00:55:43.800
Always a very powerful question to ask.

00:55:43.800 --> 00:55:48.970
The final principle of change is what I call
the action principle.

00:55:48.970 --> 00:55:51.770
And there's a reason why this principle is
at the end of the book as opposed to right

00:55:51.770 --> 00:55:52.990
at the beginning.

00:55:52.990 --> 00:55:58.080
Because if you haven't figured it out by now,
all change is emotional.

00:55:58.080 --> 00:56:00.240
Change is not about taking actions.

00:56:00.240 --> 00:56:03.840
The actions to get divorced are actually very
easy.

00:56:03.840 --> 00:56:06.410
The actions to quit smoking are really easy.

00:56:06.410 --> 00:56:08.200
The actions to lose weight are very easy.

00:56:08.200 --> 00:56:11.839
The actions to you know start a business are
pretty easy.

00:56:11.839 --> 00:56:13.670
It's the emotions that get in the way.

00:56:13.670 --> 00:56:16.670
It's all the things we've been talking about
up 'til now.

00:56:16.670 --> 00:56:21.160
With that said I would say no change happens
without some action.

00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:25.349
Once the emotions are in a place where you're
mindful about them, you actually need to get

00:56:25.349 --> 00:56:26.349
on the court.

00:56:26.349 --> 00:56:29.650
You can't just be on the stands talking about
the change all the time.

00:56:29.650 --> 00:56:31.200
You need to get on the court.

00:56:31.200 --> 00:56:35.450
So whatever change is happening ask yourself,
have I actually picked up a racket or do I

00:56:35.450 --> 00:56:37.280
just keep on talking about it?

00:56:37.280 --> 00:56:41.619
The most interesting part that I found in
the action principle with people that I interviewed

00:56:41.619 --> 00:56:43.160
was this.

00:56:43.160 --> 00:56:47.580
The most important action people took when
they go through change was to take care of

00:56:47.580 --> 00:56:49.170
their health.

00:56:49.170 --> 00:56:53.380
I mean that was incredibly interesting to
me because to me I thought, ok, they're gonna

00:56:53.380 --> 00:56:54.910
be doing a particular thing.

00:56:54.910 --> 00:56:55.910
No, no, no, no.

00:56:55.910 --> 00:57:01.320
When you're going through change, health is
the number one thing that walks out the door.

00:57:01.320 --> 00:57:03.950
You sleep less, or you sleep more.

00:57:03.950 --> 00:57:07.230
You start drinking a lot more coffee, alcohol.

00:57:07.230 --> 00:57:11.589
You've no time for exercise, 'cause now this
change has happened and it's like, I have

00:57:11.589 --> 00:57:12.589
no time.

00:57:12.589 --> 00:57:16.960
And usually you're eating a lot worse, comfort,
comfort, just to fill up the uncertainty because

00:57:16.960 --> 00:57:17.980
there's so much.

00:57:17.980 --> 00:57:21.290
So the number one thing that walks out the
door is your health.

00:57:21.290 --> 00:57:24.290
So I'd interview people and I'd be like, ok,
what really helped you?

00:57:24.290 --> 00:57:25.290
And they said one thing.

00:57:25.290 --> 00:57:26.890
He goes I took care of myself.

00:57:26.890 --> 00:57:27.920
That's it.

00:57:27.920 --> 00:57:32.820
So again sounds very simple, but the more
you take care of yourself the higher your

00:57:32.820 --> 00:57:36.270
self esteem is, the more you start you know
even just exercise.

00:57:36.270 --> 00:57:40.760
I say to a lot of people who come see me,
I've done a lot of one on one coaching.

00:57:40.760 --> 00:57:44.420
They go I'm so depressed or I'm stuck or I'm
paralyzed.

00:57:44.420 --> 00:57:49.240
They're not moving or they're dehydrated.

00:57:49.240 --> 00:57:50.380
Of course they're depressed.

00:57:50.380 --> 00:57:51.970
Nothing's moving through the body.

00:57:51.970 --> 00:57:53.410
They haven't had a proper meal.

00:57:53.410 --> 00:57:55.119
They haven't had some sleep.

00:57:55.119 --> 00:57:59.890
So it's not necessarily the emotions are whacking
you, you're not actually doing things to take

00:57:59.890 --> 00:58:03.820
care of it, so I, I came up with just a very
simple acronym, it's what I call the seed

00:58:03.820 --> 00:58:05.160
of change, S-E-E-D.

00:58:05.160 --> 00:58:09.230
This is as basic as it gets and most of you,
none of us are doing this.

00:58:09.230 --> 00:58:10.760
S is for sleep.

00:58:10.760 --> 00:58:12.130
E is for exercise.

00:58:12.130 --> 00:58:13.930
E is for eating well.

00:58:13.930 --> 00:58:16.270
And D is for drinking water.

00:58:16.270 --> 00:58:20.630
Just those things will have a massive influence
on how you go through change.

00:58:20.630 --> 00:58:25.589
The actions of change, my final point, actions
of change are small actions.

00:58:25.589 --> 00:58:30.440
People who go through change do not jump to
the top of the mountain as a metaphor for

00:58:30.440 --> 00:58:31.940
the film that's coming.

00:58:31.940 --> 00:58:33.150
It's a step at a time.

00:58:33.150 --> 00:58:34.730
It's like a woodpecker.

00:58:34.730 --> 00:58:35.730
What is the action?

00:58:35.730 --> 00:58:37.190
What's the one thing I've got to do now?

00:58:37.190 --> 00:58:38.660
What can I do today?

00:58:38.660 --> 00:58:39.660
What can I do tomorrow?

00:58:39.660 --> 00:58:41.920
Who can help me with this action tomorrow?

00:58:41.920 --> 00:58:46.440
But what are you actually doing because you
never know when that tree's gonna fall.

00:58:46.440 --> 00:58:51.810
But the actions of actually getting sort of
in the flow, that's where, where things really

00:58:51.810 --> 00:58:52.810
start happening.

00:58:52.810 --> 00:58:57.150
So again a lot more stuff to say about action,
but are you in action or are you actually

00:58:57.150 --> 00:58:58.880
in inaction?

