01:05:14.330 --> 01:05:18.060
And for people you know I often get the flip
question, which is, well, well, I don't even

01:05:18.060 --> 01:05:19.160
know what my intuition is.

01:05:19.160 --> 01:05:23.099
Which is a great question, 'cause a lot of
people it's like, there's intuition and then

01:05:23.099 --> 01:05:25.810
there's also your conditioning, right?

01:05:25.810 --> 01:05:29.230
There's like my conditioning is telling me
definitely don't do this.

01:05:29.230 --> 01:05:30.240
No, no, no.

01:05:30.240 --> 01:05:31.990
That's not your intuition.

01:05:31.990 --> 01:05:34.240
If you're confused about the two, here's where
you go.

01:05:34.240 --> 01:05:36.630
You always go to your body.

01:05:36.630 --> 01:05:39.420
Your body never lies.

01:05:39.420 --> 01:05:41.300
Are you feeling tight?

01:05:41.300 --> 01:05:43.420
Are you not sleeping?

01:05:43.420 --> 01:05:44.750
Are you nervous?

01:05:44.750 --> 01:05:45.910
Are you sweating?

01:05:45.910 --> 01:05:48.480
Are you eating or drinking more than usual?

01:05:48.480 --> 01:05:51.119
If you're about to do a deal, are you really
contracted?

01:05:51.119 --> 01:05:57.400
So for people who, you know the mind is busy,
or whatever is going on, you always go to

01:05:57.400 --> 01:05:58.400
the body.

01:05:58.400 --> 01:05:59.839
How is the body feeling?

01:05:59.839 --> 01:06:02.970
If you're invited to do something, what does
the heart want?

01:06:02.970 --> 01:06:05.730
Do I get a yes or do I get a no?

01:06:05.730 --> 01:06:11.560
And we ignore it all the time and so life
throws another change at us, and another change,

01:06:11.560 --> 01:06:16.359
and another change until we actually start
listening to what's the inner intuition?

01:06:16.359 --> 01:06:19.570
What's the microphone actually wanting to
have you say yes to?

01:06:19.570 --> 01:06:24.270
And it's hard sometimes because you've gotta
say no to things that people want you to say

01:06:24.270 --> 01:06:25.550
yes to.

01:06:25.550 --> 01:06:29.020
And you've gotta say no to things that you've
always been expected to do, right?

01:06:29.020 --> 01:06:33.970
And so there's a sense of like wanting to
please when you're going through change and

01:06:33.970 --> 01:06:36.829
yet also wanting to honor what's going on
inside.

01:06:36.829 --> 01:06:39.090
So I'd say always turning on the heart.

01:06:39.090 --> 01:06:41.040
Turning on the intuition.

01:06:41.040 --> 01:06:42.599
Listening more.

01:06:42.599 --> 01:06:45.820
Getting away from the noise and the busyness
of other people who are trying to, trying

01:06:45.820 --> 01:06:48.310
to influence you.

01:06:48.310 --> 01:06:51.440
I wouldn't say it was people who didn't make
it through change, it's people who struggled

01:06:51.440 --> 01:06:53.240
a lot through change.

01:06:53.240 --> 01:06:58.320
So when they were going through change, instead
of actually moving you know at the pace that

01:06:58.320 --> 01:07:02.920
they would have maybe liked to move, they
were stuck for the change for years and years

01:07:02.920 --> 01:07:03.920
and years.

01:07:03.920 --> 01:07:08.819
So I interviewed people who'd lost a loved
one and I could tell people who had, who had

01:07:08.819 --> 01:07:15.839
made it something beautiful and they had started
a foundation or they had done something positive

01:07:15.839 --> 01:07:21.819
or they had started celebrating that person's
passing as opposed to doing it in a very different

01:07:21.819 --> 01:07:22.819
sort of way.

01:07:22.819 --> 01:07:25.630
So life, you're gonna make it no matter what.

01:07:25.630 --> 01:07:26.680
That's a done deal.

01:07:26.680 --> 01:07:29.100
Life's gonna take care of every single one
of us.

01:07:29.100 --> 01:07:34.710
It's just a matter of how much suffering are
you gonna take on when life gives you a change

01:07:34.710 --> 01:07:35.710
to look at?

01:07:35.710 --> 01:07:39.910
I wanted to see well why is it some people
have an easier time through change?

01:07:39.910 --> 01:07:41.350
Why are they less stressed?

01:07:41.350 --> 01:07:43.370
Why are they less sad?

01:07:43.370 --> 01:07:44.619
Why are they more excited?

01:07:44.619 --> 01:07:49.360
Because you know one of the things we didn't
talk about is good changes are actually just

01:07:49.360 --> 01:07:52.360
as hard as the difficult changes, you know.

01:07:52.360 --> 01:07:53.360
People getting married.

01:07:53.360 --> 01:07:54.560
People having children.

01:07:54.560 --> 01:07:56.150
People getting promoted.

01:07:56.150 --> 01:07:59.599
People who've you know gone on and started
businesses, been very successful.

01:07:59.599 --> 01:08:05.540
The good changes bring up a lot of these same
issues, because something's changed.

01:08:05.540 --> 01:08:06.540
Right?

01:08:06.540 --> 01:08:10.060
It's just not what they thought and they don't
quite know how to deal with it.

01:08:10.060 --> 01:08:12.700
So it's not only the difficult challenging
ones.

01:08:12.700 --> 01:08:16.540
When I interviewed people, I interviewed people
who had gone through the greatest things,

01:08:16.540 --> 01:08:20.789
winning the lottery, I interviewed a few of
those people, and just how difficult it was

01:08:20.789 --> 01:08:23.819
for them to be with a positive change as well.

01:08:23.819 --> 01:08:26.219
So it wasn't make it or not make it and I
apologize if I said that.

01:08:26.219 --> 01:08:31.259
It was more, it was more the ease with which
they transitioned through change.

01:08:31.259 --> 01:08:32.519
Good question.

01:08:32.519 --> 01:08:37.319
So is it possible to help someone through
a change if they're not really willing to

01:08:37.319 --> 01:08:39.750
accept what's going on?

01:08:39.750 --> 01:08:44.809
I would say yes and the best way to help someone
through change is to be a refuge for them.

01:08:44.809 --> 01:08:51.689
And by refuge I mean they can stay in whatever
feeling they're at, place they're at, it doesn't

01:08:51.689 --> 01:08:53.679
make you feel uncomfortable.

01:08:53.679 --> 01:08:59.579
You basically allow them to be, because what
they need is love and what they need is acceptance.

01:08:59.579 --> 01:09:01.929
They don't need tips, they don't need advice.

01:09:01.929 --> 01:09:05.959
If they ask for guidance, you give it, if
not you're encroaching, right?

01:09:05.959 --> 01:09:09.469
And I've, I'm, I've been guilty of that too
as someone who likes to help people through

01:09:09.469 --> 01:09:11.710
change it's very easy to want to change.

01:09:11.710 --> 01:09:16.400
But the one place to go to is just go, what
does this person most need?

01:09:16.400 --> 01:09:17.889
That's the question.

01:09:17.889 --> 01:09:20.089
Does this person need, you know, some affection?

01:09:20.089 --> 01:09:22.489
Does this person need me to check in with
them?

01:09:22.489 --> 01:09:25.059
Does this person need a referral to someone?

01:09:25.059 --> 01:09:29.309
But it's not what you think they need, it's
really tuning in and counting on what does

01:09:29.309 --> 01:09:30.549
this person need.

01:09:30.549 --> 01:09:38.069
But it's, it's a radical acceptance of who
they are and it's also a seeing of who they're

01:09:38.069 --> 01:09:39.670
gonna be on the other end of this.

01:09:39.670 --> 01:09:45.569
So if you can already hold a vision for how
they're gonna be when they get through this,

01:09:45.569 --> 01:09:48.089
they start feeling that when they're around
you.

01:09:48.089 --> 01:09:49.789
They don't feel stuck around you.

01:09:49.789 --> 01:09:52.159
You've already seen them move through the
challenge.

01:09:52.159 --> 01:09:53.359
You've already seen them healthy.

01:09:53.359 --> 01:09:57.270
You've already seen them in a relationship
or whatever it is that they're looking to

01:09:57.270 --> 01:09:58.270
be in.

01:09:58.270 --> 01:09:59.389
Thank you very much.

01:09:59.389 --> 01:10:00.090
[audience applause]

